This paper discusses the coexistence of networks that communicate status updates in real-time, which is a topic related to networked systems and communication (cs.NI). The paper also uses game theory to model the behavior of the networks, which falls under the category of game theory and economics (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization of age and throughput, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper mentions the use of wireless spectrum, which is a topic related to multimedia (cs.MM).
